\pard\f0\fs28   {\b  L. paradoxum} A. Bolós & Font Quer,{\i  Collect. Bot.} ({\i Barcelona}){\b  1}: 297 (1947), from the Pyrenees, is a variant of{\b  10} with hairs at the junctions of the branches of the leaves and with considerable development of the pericarp over the primary ridges, rather as in {\i Guillonea}. Intermediates between this extreme form and the typical plant occur in N.E. Spain.
