\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 1. T. villosa} L., {\i Sp. Pl.} 261 (1753). Somewhat pubescent, pruinose perennial 30-200 cm. Stock with abundant fibres. Stem terete, striate, solid. Lower leaves 20-35 × 10-30 cm, 3- to 4-pinnate, more or less villous to hispidulous on rhachis and lamina; lobes 5-15 mm, rarely (var.{\i  platyphyllos} P. Silva & Franco) up to 30 mm, ovate-oblong to oblong in outline, dentate or shallowly lobed; teeth with a spinous mucro; petioles of upper cauline leaves inflated, without lamina. Rays 9-24. Bracts and bracteoles few or none. Fruit 8-15 mm, elliptical; lateral wings 2-3 mm wide, deeply emarginate at base and apex; dorsal ridges not or very narrowly winged.{\i  Portugal to S. France.} Ga Hs Lu.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 2. T. maxima} Miller,{\i  Gard. Dict.} ed. 8, no. 2 (1768). Like {\b 1} but nearly glabrous; lower leaves up to 50 cm, pinnate, ovate in outline; lobes 50-120 mm, ovate-oblong in outline, dentate or shallowly lobed, often decurrent; fruit 7-10 mm. •{\i  C. & S. Spain, E. & S. Portugal.} Hs Lu.
